1
00:01:46,565 --> 00:01:51,528
2.. 5..7.. 10 minutes.. he continued to stare.

2
00:01:52,279 --> 00:01:54,740
I ignored him at first but then I went to the table..

3
00:01:54,740 --> 00:01:56,908
...and I said, any problem, sir?

4
00:01:57,534 --> 00:01:58,869
I'm very sorry.

5
00:01:58,869 --> 00:02:01,705
You look like someone I know, he replied

6
00:02:02,289 --> 00:02:03,832
I was going to walk away..

7
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:05,709
...but he was a 70 year old man.

8
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:07,169
Horny uncle!

9
00:02:08,669 --> 00:02:11,882
Anyway, so I had to ask him whom did I look like.

10
00:02:12,758 --> 00:02:14,092
Any guesses on his reply?

11
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:15,635
His mother?

12
00:02:15,886 --> 00:02:17,429
His daughter.

13
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:20,390
His 8th grade biology teacher.

14
00:02:20,682 --> 00:02:22,225
Don't try to fit in your fantasy here.

15
00:02:22,225 --> 00:02:25,062
She was so hot, Mrs. Matthews.. I promise. Oh my god!

16
00:02:25,062 --> 00:02:29,191
He said I look like his dog.

17
00:02:32,736 --> 00:02:34,529
What? I'm serious!

18
00:02:35,072 --> 00:02:37,657
I'm serious. His dog was called Princess.

19
00:02:37,657 --> 00:02:38,617
That's a terrible name.

20
00:02:38,617 --> 00:02:40,327
Forget the name, listen to the story.

21
00:02:40,327 --> 00:02:43,205
I said, you made fun of me, uncle. Can I go home now?

22
00:02:43,663 --> 00:02:46,583
He said, please listen to me.

23
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:51,129
Princess died in a car accident in 1985.

24
00:02:51,630 --> 00:02:55,175
She freed herself and ran into an oncoming car.

25
00:02:55,634 --> 00:02:58,637
The car ran over her and by the time he reached there, she was dead.

26
00:02:58,637 --> 00:03:00,764
She was dead. Her throat was crushed.

27
00:03:01,223 --> 00:03:03,600
This happened on 17th June, 1985.

28
00:03:04,059 --> 00:03:05,185
- You're joking.
- No.

29
00:03:05,811 --> 00:03:07,104
That's my birthdate.

30
00:03:07,354 --> 00:03:08,647
- No..
- Yeah!

31
00:03:09,064 --> 00:03:12,401
And it gets stranger because I have a birth mark on my neck.

32
00:03:12,401 --> 00:03:13,527
Lying!

33
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:16,029
I have a birth mark on my neck.

34
00:03:16,947 --> 00:03:17,948
See!

35
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:25,288
Very funny.

36
00:03:26,289 --> 00:03:28,333
Shaan.. I'm sorry.

37
00:03:28,834 --> 00:03:31,753
Shaan.. Shaan!

38
00:04:19,593 --> 00:04:21,428
Gulp it down, you'll feel better.

39
00:04:27,225 --> 00:04:28,351
What happened?

40
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:31,480
Half of the critics hadn't Even arrived, you should've waited.

41
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:34,316
I don't know why but I suddenly felt so weird.

42
00:04:34,316 --> 00:04:38,028
I saw something that wasn't actually there, but it felt so real.

43
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:40,071
I don't understand what you are saying, Mehak

44
00:04:40,572 --> 00:04:41,573
I don't know.

45
00:04:42,324 --> 00:04:44,409
- You're okay now, right?
- Yes.

46
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:47,037
Because everyone really liked your work.

47
00:04:47,037 --> 00:04:48,538
- You think?
- Yes.

48
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:53,793
Stop, pull over.

49
00:04:57,964 --> 00:04:58,965
Come up.

50
00:04:59,424 --> 00:05:00,425
Why?

51
00:05:02,177 --> 00:05:04,137
We'll have a drink, listen to some music.

52
00:05:04,679 --> 00:05:05,680
You know..

53
00:05:06,515 --> 00:05:07,849
Just because it happened once after getting drunk..

54
00:05:07,849 --> 00:05:09,643
...doesn't mean it's gonna happen every time.

55
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:20,237
You know what, I don't know about your past life..

56
00:05:20,529 --> 00:05:24,533
But in this life you definitely are.. a princess

57
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:27,661
Bye-bye.

58
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:30,789
- Bye!
- Goodnight.

59
00:05:30,789 --> 00:05:31,790
Goodnight.

60
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:46,573
Hello.. madam?

61
00:08:21,543 --> 00:08:22,544
Oh my God!

62
00:08:23,795 --> 00:08:25,880
- Ma'am, are you ok?
- Ma'am, are you ok?

63
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:27,799
- Get some water!
- What happened?

64
00:08:27,799 --> 00:08:29,676
- She's bleeding!
- Get some water.

65
00:08:29,676 --> 00:08:31,344
- What happened?
- Have you found any ID?

66
00:08:43,773 --> 00:08:46,276
Mehak, open your mouth. Show your tongue.

67
00:08:46,651 --> 00:08:49,821
Hold my hand. You're in a hospital, I'm a doctor. Just relax.

68
00:08:50,113 --> 00:08:52,949
Show your tongue. Calm down. You're in hospital. Open your eyes.

69
00:08:53,324 --> 00:08:56,536
Open your eyes.

70
00:09:28,943 --> 00:09:32,322
C'mon, Mehak. The doctor has been waiting for long.

71
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:44,459
I was six and you were around three years old.

72
00:09:44,459 --> 00:09:46,795
Do you remember the terrace on our Jammu home?

73
00:09:47,629 --> 00:09:49,923
I was spinning you around in circles..

74
00:09:49,923 --> 00:09:52,133
...when you suddenly slipped out of my hand.

75
00:09:52,801 --> 00:09:54,260
You fell to the ground floor.

76
00:09:55,053 --> 00:09:57,430
Do you remember that song that dad sang to calm you down..

77
00:10:24,374 --> 00:10:27,418
Relax, Mehak. You can't step out right..

78
00:10:27,919 --> 00:10:30,880
...that's why I've brought the outside world to you here.

79
00:10:32,715 --> 00:10:34,133
Oh my god!

80
00:10:35,969 --> 00:10:37,345
This is virtual therapy.

81
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:42,100
For people like you. Go on, walk ahead.

82
00:10:48,189 --> 00:10:49,691
Very good, Mehak.

83
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:52,068
Do you like shopping?

84
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:55,613
Anusha told me that you always did the grocery shopping.

85
00:10:56,906 --> 00:10:58,783
C'mon, Mehak, keep going.

86
00:11:01,786 --> 00:11:04,956
That's good, Mehak. So what do you feel like buying today?

87
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:06,875
Buy me a chocolate, aunty.

88
00:11:06,875 --> 00:11:08,793
Yes, pick up a chocolate for Joey.

89
00:11:10,044 --> 00:11:12,171
- You can do it, Mehak.
- The biscuit ones.

90
00:11:12,881 --> 00:11:14,632
Biscuit chocolate, c'mon Mehak.

91
00:11:15,425 --> 00:11:17,343
Where's the chocolate?

92
00:11:17,677 --> 00:11:19,137
There are people there.

93
00:11:19,137 --> 00:11:21,180
- Please.. please..
- No, no.

94
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:24,267
Please don't touch it. Mehak. Please don't touch it.

95
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:25,685
Keep going.

96
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:28,938
You're almost there, Mehak. Relax.

97
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:32,358
Look for the chocolate.

98
00:11:34,402 --> 00:11:36,195
You can do it, Mehak.

99
00:11:37,572 --> 00:11:40,158
Be brave. Very good.

100
00:11:45,204 --> 00:11:46,623
- She hit me.
- Who hit you?

101
00:11:46,623 --> 00:11:48,833
- Relax.. relax..
- She hit me! She hit me!

102
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:51,085
Relax. Mehak! Mehak!

103
00:11:51,085 --> 00:11:53,463
- Mummy!
- She hit me!

104
00:11:53,463 --> 00:11:54,756
- Calm down.
- Mummy!

105
00:11:54,756 --> 00:11:56,966
- Relax, relax.
- Don't touch me!

106
00:11:57,675 --> 00:11:59,385
Mehak!

107
00:12:02,889 --> 00:12:04,807
- What happened to aunty?
- Nothing.

108
00:12:06,643 --> 00:12:08,853
Go, get your drawing book.

109
00:12:14,776 --> 00:12:17,862
I'm sorry, Anusha. Mehak suffers from Agoraphobia.

110
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:22,492
She has a deep-seated fear of the outside world.

111
00:12:22,951 --> 00:12:25,578
She's not being difficult, she's just unwell.

112
00:12:26,371 --> 00:12:29,791
If not treated, Mehak can become completely unstable.

113
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:33,795
She is certain that if she steps out of the house..

114
00:12:33,795 --> 00:12:35,713
She will be made to experience the same horror she went through that
night.

115
00:12:35,713 --> 00:12:38,216
But that taxi driver is in prison.

116
00:12:38,216 --> 00:12:40,134
Mehak knows that very well.

117
00:12:40,134 --> 00:12:41,469
He can't do anything now.

118
00:12:41,469 --> 00:12:44,097
What happened that night? It's not like she was raped!

119
00:12:50,937 --> 00:12:55,817
I understand, Anusha. If you want, you can admit her to the clinic.

120
00:12:56,192 --> 00:12:58,778
- There is a good clinic in Byculla..
- Just a second, doctor.

121
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:02,824
There's no need to put Mehak in an institution. And please, she's
not crazy.

122
00:13:10,373 --> 00:13:11,416
Take it.

123
00:13:13,793 --> 00:13:14,919
Thanks.

124
00:13:26,264 --> 00:13:28,558
I don't want to talk, I just need some time.

125
00:13:29,183 --> 00:13:31,811
Do you know how long its been since you stepped out of this house?

126
00:13:32,103 --> 00:13:33,354
- Two weeks.
- Two?

127
00:13:34,939 --> 00:13:36,357
- Four.
- Yes, four weeks.

128
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:38,151
Not four weeks, but four months.

129
00:13:40,111 --> 00:13:41,112
That's true.

130
00:13:44,449 --> 00:13:45,908
What crap!

131
00:13:46,784 --> 00:13:49,495
Mehak, I have other responsibilities as well.

132
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:50,747
Did you see Joey today?

133
00:13:50,747 --> 00:13:52,832
He gets so frightened seeing you that he can't sleep at night.

134
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:55,293
Then why do you call that therapist home?

135
00:13:56,252 --> 00:13:58,337
What have I done? It's always my fault!

136
00:13:58,337 --> 00:14:01,716
He is a five year old kid, don't you feel he deserves some normalcy?

137
00:14:03,551 --> 00:14:04,927
Are you blaming me for that?

138
00:14:05,928 --> 00:14:08,639
- If he wants normalcy, take him to his father.
- Mehak.

139
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:11,642
Her kid gets screwed up, is it my responsibility?

140
00:14:11,642 --> 00:14:13,436
Mehak, it's not necessary to involve him.

141
00:14:13,436 --> 00:14:15,646
And I'm just talking about Joey, let's just stay there.

142
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:18,149
- What happened last week? Tell him.
- Get lost seriously.

143
00:14:18,608 --> 00:14:20,359
Joey returns from school and rings the doorbell.

144
00:14:20,359 --> 00:14:22,862
But he isn't able to get into the house. Why?

145
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:24,655
- I wanna know that.
- How many times will she say that!

146
00:14:24,655 --> 00:14:25,782
- Exactly!
- She's said it thrice already!

147
00:14:25,782 --> 00:14:28,534
I'll say it again and again, the kid stood on the street for four
hours.

148
00:14:28,534 --> 00:14:30,161
Why couldn't he get into the house?

149
00:14:30,161 --> 00:14:33,748
Because you couldn't go upto the door and let him in.

150
00:14:33,748 --> 00:14:34,791
- Yes.
- Yes, so?

151
00:14:34,791 --> 00:14:37,919
- I said I'm sorry.
- What if something had happened to the kid?

152
00:14:40,671 --> 00:14:42,673
- I'm sorry.
- What do I do?

153
00:14:43,925 --> 00:14:45,802
What do I do? Quit my job?

154
00:14:46,803 --> 00:14:50,515
Shall I shop for normalcy from that virtual supermarket for you?

155
00:14:50,515 --> 00:14:51,516
What do you want?

156
00:14:52,141 --> 00:14:53,935
- What do you want?
- What do you want?

157
00:14:53,935 --> 00:14:55,520
You want to send me to an institution!

158
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:56,646
- I don't want to send you to an institution..
- Shut up!

159
00:14:56,646 --> 00:14:58,356
I heard you.

160
00:14:58,356 --> 00:14:59,649
- What did you hear?
- Mehak.

161
00:15:00,525 --> 00:15:01,692
I'm feeling dizzy.

162
00:15:01,943 --> 00:15:05,321
Ok.. calm down.. sit down.

163
00:15:05,780 --> 00:15:06,781
Sit down.

164
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:08,866
Look, Mehak.

165
00:15:09,117 --> 00:15:11,661
You can't throw me out of my own house.

166
00:15:12,203 --> 00:15:14,288
- This house belongs to me too.
- Of course, Mehak.

167
00:15:14,288 --> 00:15:15,706
It'll always be your house.

168
00:15:16,332 --> 00:15:18,042
I'm just telling you that..

169
00:15:19,127 --> 00:15:20,169
Mehak?

170
00:15:24,966 --> 00:15:28,261
Anusha, be strong. We need to do this.

171
00:15:29,387 --> 00:15:30,847
I don't know if we're doing the right thing.

172
00:15:30,847 --> 00:15:33,266
Anu, I'm taking responsibility.

173
00:15:36,102 --> 00:15:38,771
Trust me, she'll become fine in a new place. Away from you guys.

174
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:50,575
Jiya?

175
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,334
Jiya?

176
00:16:02,503 --> 00:16:03,963
Jiya!

177
00:16:07,758 --> 00:16:08,801
Oh!

178
00:16:09,260 --> 00:16:11,596
Hi, ma'am - Go!

179
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:13,973
- Who are you?
- I didn't do anything.

180
00:16:14,390 --> 00:16:17,685
Mehak.. please.. calm down.

181
00:16:18,352 --> 00:16:19,437
Relax.

182
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:22,481
- It's me.
- Where were you?

183
00:16:26,402 --> 00:16:28,321
I can't.. I can't move.

184
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:29,697
You got scared.

185
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:32,116
Who are you? How did you get in?

186
00:16:32,116 --> 00:16:33,284
The door was open.

187
00:16:34,243 --> 00:16:37,121
I'm Manu. Manu Malhotra, your next-door neighbour.

188
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:38,206
I stay in 602.

189
00:16:38,206 --> 00:16:40,541
I'm so sorry if I frightened you.

190
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:42,877
- I thought that Jiya was back.
- Jiya?

191
00:16:42,877 --> 00:16:44,879
Jiya is my friend.

192
00:16:44,879 --> 00:16:47,173
- Manu, actually we've just moved in. Let us settle down first.
- Of course.

193
00:16:47,173 --> 00:16:48,674
- If you need anything.
- Sure.

194
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:50,426
- Please don't hesitate, I'm just a doorbell away.
- Thank you.

195
00:16:50,426 --> 00:16:51,677
- Shall I make tea for you?
- No.

196
00:16:51,677 --> 00:16:53,221
Water..

197
00:16:53,221 --> 00:16:54,931
- I'll give it, thank you.
- I want water.

198
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:58,059
- How about coffee..
- No, Thanks, Manu.

199
00:17:00,978 --> 00:17:03,439
- He's laughing.
- I didn't arrange the welcome party.

200
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:04,690
Where's the house?

201
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:06,358
This is going to be your house for sometime now.

202
00:17:06,358 --> 00:17:07,484
100 years later?

203
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:12,573
You are very young.

204
00:17:13,156 --> 00:17:15,659
This is my friend's house, it's been lying vacant.

205
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:17,787
We can stay here as long as we want.

206
00:17:18,371 --> 00:17:21,499
- We?
- You, of course. C'mon, get up now.

207
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:24,794
- Come.
- Get up. Do this, do that.

208
00:17:24,794 --> 00:17:26,796
I've asked Anu for some time..

209
00:17:26,796 --> 00:17:28,881
...because there's no point sending you to a clinic.

210
00:17:29,507 --> 00:17:32,176
Being independent again will help you face this problem. Really.

211
00:17:34,929 --> 00:17:35,930
Will you give it a try?

212
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:46,357
Best keep this one closed.

213
00:17:55,574 --> 00:17:56,909
The bedroom has such a nice view.

214
00:17:57,451 --> 00:18:00,079
- Shaan, please close it.
- No, you need vitamin D.

215
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:04,875
Who does this belong to?

216
00:18:05,793 --> 00:18:09,463
The house belongs to my friend but he had rented it out to a girl
named Jiya.

217
00:18:09,463 --> 00:18:11,257
Some of her clothes and stuff might be lying around.

218
00:18:11,257 --> 00:18:12,633
Throw away whatever you don't need.

219
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:15,219
- What if she comes back for it?
- She won't.

220
00:18:15,219 --> 00:18:16,220
What?

221
00:18:16,679 --> 00:18:19,598
She didn't pay the rent, didn't come to collect her deposit.

222
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:21,392
Maybe she skipped town.

223
00:18:33,029 --> 00:18:34,280
Sorry, chips.

224
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:38,659
Shall we clean up the place?

225
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:41,537
I'll do it. Don't you have to go to work?

226
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:43,873
I thought I'll take my Diwali leave from today itself.

227
00:18:43,873 --> 00:18:45,041
No need, Shaan.

228
00:18:45,041 --> 00:18:47,335
I'll take some time out of my busy schedule.

229
00:18:49,295 --> 00:18:51,756
- How much is the rent?
- Don't worry about that.

230
00:18:54,675 --> 00:18:57,678
Get well soon, start painting and you can pay me back, ok?

231
00:18:57,678 --> 00:18:59,722
What did you and Anusha put in my coffee?

232
00:19:00,681 --> 00:19:02,183
You thought I'll not come to know.

233
00:19:02,767 --> 00:19:04,518
Would you've agreed if I had asked directly?

234
00:19:06,395 --> 00:19:09,357
If my motor skills don't come back. I'm not talking to you again.

235
00:19:11,776 --> 00:19:13,027
You should go now.

236
00:19:13,819 --> 00:19:15,279
Don't forget your medicines.

237
00:23:03,340 --> 00:23:06,927
"This girl is going to drive me crazy"

238
00:25:04,253 --> 00:25:05,421
Hello?

239
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:02,186
Don't need

240
00:26:26,877 --> 00:26:27,878
Don't need.

241
00:26:58,617 --> 00:27:00,869
- Hi, it's me. Open up.
- Wait a second!

242
00:27:02,830 --> 00:27:05,833
- I'm opening, but count to ten before you step in. Ok?
- Yeah, ok.

243
00:27:06,124 --> 00:27:07,334
- Huh?
- Yeah!

244
00:27:07,334 --> 00:27:08,335
Ok.

245
00:27:14,383 --> 00:27:15,634
Shall I come in?

246
00:28:16,069 --> 00:28:17,070
What are you doing?

247
00:28:17,654 --> 00:28:18,655
Nothing.

248
00:28:26,455 --> 00:28:28,832
Hey, dance with me, c'mon.

249
00:28:29,166 --> 00:28:30,167
- C'mon.
- No, thanks.

250
00:28:30,167 --> 00:28:31,168
C'mon!

251
00:28:31,960 --> 00:28:34,546
- What are you doing? Let me eat.
- C'mon, play along.

252
00:28:34,796 --> 00:28:38,342
Ok, fine. I'll watch you dance. Shaan's got talent - M, c'mon!

253
00:30:07,264 --> 00:30:09,224
